TY  - JOUR
T1  - Fund Manager Use of Public Information: New Evidence on Managerial Skills
AU  - KACPERCZYK, MARCIN
AU  - SERU, AMIT
Y1  - 2007/04/01
PY  - 2007
DA  - 2007/04/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.2007.01215.x
T2  - The Journal of Finance
JF  - The Journal of Finance
JO  - The Journal of Finance
JA  - The Journal of Finance
SP  - 485
EP  - 528
VL  - 62
IS  - 2
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0022-1082
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.2007.01215.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - ABSTRACT We show theoretically that the responsiveness of a fund manager's portfolio allocations to changes in public information decreases in the manager's skill. We go on to estimate this sensitivity (RPI) as the R2 of the regression of changes in a manager's portfolio holdings on changes in public information using a panel of U.S. equity funds. Consistent with RPI containing information related to managerial skills, we find a strong inverse relationship between RPI and various existing measures of performance, and between RPI and fund flows. We also document that both fund- and manager-specific attributes affect RPI.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - Managerial Ability, Compensation, and the Closed-End Fund Discount
AU  - BERK, JONATHAN B.
AU  - STANTON, RICHARD
Y1  - 2007/04/01
PY  - 2007
DA  - 2007/04/01
